data.description: Located between Redding and Burney. Escape to a tranquil haven of privacy and embrace the quintessential country lifestyle with this exceptional property located at 16970 Buzzard Roost Rd in Round Mountain, California. Situated on a sprawling 15-acre parcel, this remarkable place offers the perfect blend of serene living, spacious interiors, and the opportunity to create your dream rural oasis. With 15 acres at your disposal, this property presents endless possibilities. The generous land allows for the addition of a mother-in-law unit, a horse barn, and any other outdoor pursuits you envision. Step into the sunroom entry adorned with elegant tile flooring, setting the tone for the warm and welcoming ambiance that pervades the entire home. Boasting 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and an executive office with a grand double door entry, this home caters to your modern needs. A 4th room, while lacking a closet, provides the opportunity for a private space and has an extra area for an addition office or kids' playroom. The heart of the home is the spacious open kitchen featuring a large island, accent pendant lighting, and a large pantry. Equipped with double ovens and a gas stove, it's a culinary enthusiast's dream. The large formal dining area offers an ideal setting for hosting gatherings, while valuated ceilings and abundant natural light throughout create an inviting and airy atmosphere. Enjoy the privacy of a split floor plan w/ the master bedroom offering an oversized walk-in closet and an ensuite bathroom complete with a soaking tub, walk-in shower, & dual vanity sinks. An attached office or den provides additional flexibility. A 30x24 oversized shop/garage provides ample space for storage, projects, or hobbies, further enhancing the functionality of the property. The property is par fenced with front gates, ensuring both security and a sense of seclusion. A natural Artesian spring and a productive well provide water sources for your ventures. Nestled conveniently between Redding, and Burney, CA.
